    <div class="content" id="content">
    <h7>PhD Program </h7>  &nbsp; 

    



<p>


The PhD program in Mathematical Modelling and Methods will begin enrollment for the program starting September 2016.

<h4>This program consists of three main fields of study:</h4>

</p>

<p>
<ol>
	  <li>Discrete Mathematics and Networks</li>
	  <li>Financial Mathematics</li>
	  <li>Biomathematics and Fluids</li>
</ol>
</p>


 <p>

The requirements of the program consist of three (3) one-term elective courses, regular attendance of the doctoral student seminar,
the candidacy exam with written  and oral components and the thesis work, culminating in the oral defense of the doctoral thesis.
For more information about the program, please contact the Program Administrator, Sally Yang at 
<a href="mailto:mathgrad@ryerson.ca">mathgrad@ryerson.ca</a>. 
</p> 


 
      
